- Documentation: https://canarytrace.com/docs/

## Visualizations

**Smoke checks**

Count of opened and analyzed URL's in a real browser.

**Checks**

On the tested page exist functional defect, or the response code higher than 399 or it cannot be opened during 60s limit.

**Select smoke URL**

Select a specific url, otherwise the displayed data will show all smokes.

**MAX load time**

Load time for every URL, given in milliseconds, should be accurate to 5 µs (microseconds).

**MAX performance entries**

Displays Response Time, TTFB, and LoadEventEnd metrics for every resources, such as home page, css files or images.

**Smoke load page table**

Displays 90th percentile and MAX of load time and TTFB.

**Performance entries overview**

Displays TOP resources with MAX load time.

**TOP errors**

Displays TOP functional errors.

---
Do you find mistake or have any questions? Please create issue, thanks 👍
https://github.com/canarytrace/documentation/issues/new/choose

attributes.title: Performance Audit Manual (canarytrace)
attributes.visState:
{"title":"Performance Audit Manual (canarytrace)","type":"markdown","aggs":[],"params":{"fontSize":12,"openLinksInNewTab":true,"markdown":"# Performance audit

- Documentation: https://canarytrace.com/docs/

### Visualizations

First visualizations are chevrons with important performance metrics. Your goal is approach of 100 score of each metrics.

**Uri**

Please select target URL and emulated device.

**Performance score line**

Shows a performance metric from Lighthouse.

**Core Web Vitals**

Are user-centric metrics [defined by Google](https://web.dev/vitals/).

**Backend vs frontend**

Metrics Server Backend Latency and First Contentful Paint are useful for comparisons where a slowdown has occurred. 

**Audit metrics**

Other useful metrics for monitoring web application and browser performance.

**Main thread task**

Shows a long tasks that the browser had to process. 

**Audit resources**

Shows count of resources downloaded into browser.

### Metrics and Score
**First Contentful Paint**

First Contentful Paint marks the time at which the first text or image is painted. [Learn more](https://web.dev/first-contentful-paint). Weight 15%

**Speed Index**

Speed Index shows how quickly the contents of a page are visibly populated. [Learn more](https://web.dev/speed-index). Weight 15%

**Largest Contentful Paint**

Largest Contentful Paint marks the time at which the largest text or image is painted. [Learn more](https://web.dev/lighthouse-largest-contentful-paint). Weight 25%

**Time to Interactive**

Time to interactive is the amount of time it takes for the page to become fully interactive. [Learn more](https://web.dev/interactive). Weight 15%

**Total Blocking Time**

Sum of all time periods between FCP and Time to Interactive, when task length exceeded 50ms, expressed in milliseconds. [Learn more](https://web.dev/lighthouse-total-blocking-time). Weight 25%

**Cumulative Layout Shift**

Cumulative Layout Shift measures the movement of visible elements within the viewport. [Learn more](https://web.dev/cls). Weight 5%


**How scores are color-coded**

The metrics scores and the perf score are colored according to these ranges:

- 0 to 49 (grey/red): Poor
- 50 to 89 (orange): Needs Improvement
- 90 to 100 (green): Good

_Based on [Lighthouse 8.0.0](https://googlechrome.github.io/lighthouse/scorecalc/)_

---
Do you find mistake or have any questions? Please create issue, thanks 👍
https://github.com/canarytrace/documentation/issues/new/choose
"}}
